 car sprite in the center of the screen simply hot-swaps through its pre-re=
ndered frames.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"16">Because the car's frame updat=
es exactly in sync with the floor's rotation vector, your brain stitches th=
e two disparate systems together. You perceive a camera orbiting a volumetr=
ic 3D machine, but in reality, you are watching a flat map spin under a 2D =
flipbook.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"17">It is the exact same philosophy yo=
u applied by fixing the chassis vector to the floor grid while mapping the =
upper torso frame strictly to the mouse target vector. You cheat the Z-axis=
 by isolating the math.</p></div></message-content><!----></div></structure=
